The paper deals with community detection in dynamic graphs, which is a problem that falls under the scope of social network analysis and machine learning. The paper proposes a new technique called $\Delta-screening$ that can be incorporated into any community detection method that uses modularity as its objective function for clustering. This technique is generic and can be applied to a wide range of dynamic graphs, making it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with the analysis of social networks and the information that flows through them. The paper's focus on community detection in dynamic graphs aligns with the research interests of this sub-category. 

cs.SD (Software Engineering) is the second most likely sub-category as the paper proposes a new technique that can be incorporated into existing community detection methods. This technique can improve the performance of these methods, making it relevant to software engineering.
